    Oncology Phase I Trial Design and Conduct: Time for a Change MDICT Guidelines 2022.
The phase I dose escalation trial should define the recommended dose range for later testing in randomized phase 2 trials, rather than a single recommended phase 2 dose, and consider scenarios where different populations may require different dosages. The adoption of these recommendation will improve dosage selection in early clinical trials of new anti-cancer treatments and ultimately, outcomes for patients.
